One way to replace characters within a range of ascii valus is to treat the string as a `char[]`, select all the characters except the ones you don&#39;t want (those with an ascii value between 126 and 255), and then `Concat` the string together again:

    line = string.Concat(line.Where(chr =&gt; chr &lt; 126 || chr &gt; 255));

